From: Alex Elder <elder@inktank.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jul 2012 09:09:27 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 152/938] rbd: simplify __rbd_remove_all_snaps()
References: fate#312983
Git-commit: a05932905695f8c6c06d353ecd52c8e5d607cc77
Patch-mainline: v3.6-rc1

This just replaces a while loop with list_for_each_entry_safe()
in __rbd_remove_all_snaps().

Signed-off-by: Alex Elder <elder@inktank.com>
Reviewed-by: Josh Durgin <josh.durgin@inktank.com>
Acked-by: Danny Al-Gaaf <dalgaaf@suse.de>

---
 drivers/block/rbd.c | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/block/rbd.c b/drivers/block/rbd.c
index b9895fe..74e6a33 100644
--- a/drivers/block/rbd.c
+++ b/drivers/block/rbd.c
@@ -1692,11 +1692,10 @@ bad:
 static void __rbd_remove_all_snaps(struct rbd_device *rbd_dev)
 {
 	struct rbd_snap *snap;
+	struct rbd_snap *next;
 
-	while (!list_empty(&rbd_dev->snaps)) {
-		snap = list_first_entry(&rbd_dev->snaps, struct rbd_snap, node);
+	list_for_each_entry_safe(snap, next, &rbd_dev->snaps, node)
 		__rbd_remove_snap_dev(rbd_dev, snap);
-	}
 }
 
